olive oil
1 margherita-style pizza with cherry tomatoes & basil pesto
1 cucumber
1 bag spinach & rocket mix
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced
• Bake margherita-style pizzas directly on wire oven racks until cheese is melted and golden, 12-15 minutes.

TIP: Placing the pizzas directly onto the wire racks helps the base to crisp up.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice cucumber.
• In a medium bowl, combine cucumber, spinach & rocket mix, grated Parmesan cheese and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

• Slice margherita and pesto pizza.
• Divide pizza slices between plates.
• Serve with cucumber and Parmesan salad. Enjoy!